<!-- WHO WE ARE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3">Who We Are</h2>
    <p class="text-muted mb-3">
  The Solar Energy Society of Nigeria (SESN) was inaugurated in March 1980 at the Project Development Institute (PRODA), Enugu, and officially launched on 11th July of the same year. The Society was established to promote the development and application of solar energy technologies in Nigeria.
</p>

<p class="text-muted mb-3">
  The Society was founded by distinguished academics and professionals, including Professor A.O.E. Animalu (Foundation President), Professor G.O. Ezekwe, Professor C.C.O. Ezeilo, Professor U.A. Akinsote, Professor R.I. Salawu, and several other notable contributors from leading Nigerian institutions.
</p>

<p class="text-muted">
  Since its inception, SESN has played a vital role in advancing renewable energy through research, collaboration, and advocacy. The Society organizes the annual National Solar Energy Forum (NASEF), which brings together experts, researchers, policymakers, and industry stakeholders to drive innovation and sustainable energy development across Nigeria.
</p>
  </div>
</section>

